title: Five Facts About NASA’s Moon Bound Technology
description: NASA is sending revolutionary technologies to the Moon aboard Intuitive Machines’ second lunar delivery as part of the agency’s CLPS (Commercial Lunar Payload Services) initiative and Artemis campaign to establish a long-term presence on the lunar surface.  As part of this CLPS flight to the Moon, NASA’s Space Technology Mission Directorate will test novel technologies to […]
author: Stefanie Payne
categories: Research and Technology at Kennedy Space Center

title: NASA to Provide Coverage of Progress 91 Launch, Space Station Docking
description: NASA will provide live launch and docking coverage of a Roscosmos cargo spacecraft delivering approximately three tons of food, fuel, and supplies for the crew aboard the International Space Station. The unpiloted Roscosmos Progress 91 spacecraft is scheduled to launch at 4:24 p.m. EST, Thursday, Feb. 27 (2:24 a.m. Baikonur time, Friday, Feb. 28), on […]
author: Tiernan P. Doyle

title: Intuitive Machines' lunar lander Athena set to blast off to the moon
description: A SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket is about to launch a number of missions, including a private lunar lander, a lunar satellite for NASA and a prospecting probe for an asteroid-mining company

title: Huge thunderstorm on Jupiter captured in best detail ever seen
description: NASA's Juno spacecraft swooped in for a close look at a massive thunderstorm on Jupiter, revealing that it may have similarities to storms on Earth

title: Mars once had an ocean with sandy beaches, researchers say
description: China’s Zhurong rover finds evidence of shoreline buried deep undergroundMars may not seem like a prime holiday spot with its arid landscape and punishing radiation levels, but it once boasted beaches, researchers have found.While previous discoveries of features including valley networks and sedimentary rocks has suggested the red planet once had flowing rivers, there has been debate among scientists over whether it also had oceans. Continue reading...
author: Nicola Davis Science correspondent

title: Chance of giant asteroid hitting Earth in 2032 falls to 0.0017%
description: Asteroid 2024 YR4 had reached a 3.1% likelihood of impact but further data has rendered it negligibleIt was a discovery that lead to panic-inducing headlines: a giant asteroid found to be hurtling towards Earth that, while unlikely to wipe out life, could do some serious damage.But now the world can breathe a sigh of relief. After the odds of a future collision rose earlier this year, the likelihood of an impact is now so low as to be negligible. Continue reading...
author: Nicola Davis Science correspondent

title: SpaceX wraps up investigation of Starship Flight 7 explosion (video)
description: SpaceX has finished its investigation into what went wrong on the seventh test flight of its Starship rocket, which ended with a dramatic explosion.

title: SpaceX targeting Feb. 28 for next launch of Starship megarocket
description: SpaceX plans to launch the eighth test flight of its Starship megarocket on Friday (Feb. 28), company founder and CEO Elon Musk says.
